1. Shared VPC:
- Shared VPC allows an organization to connect resources from multiple projects
  to a common VPC network.
- Allows the resources to communicate with each other securely and efficiently
  using internal IPs from that network.
- designate a project as a host project and attach one or more other service
  projects to it.
- Each project has an instance with has an interface in VPC of host project.
- security and network policy occurs in a single designated VPC network.

2. VPC Peering:
- Connect accross two VPC networks, regardless of whether they belong to the
  same project or the same organization.
- Decentralized:
  - each VPC network can remain under the control of separate administrator
    groups and maintains its own global firewall and routing tables.
